  "reviewFindings": [
    "no blockers — all 77 epub tests pass, ruff clean, no staged files"
  ],
  "manualNotes": "The 16 M4 FFmpeg failures are not regressions introduced by M5 work. They were present before this session and affect only pipeline/e2e tests. A follow-up task should add a pytest skip guard (e.g. @pytest.mark.requires_ffmpeg with conftest detection) to prevent these from polluting CI when FFmpeg loudnorm is unavailable or misconfigured."
}
```

